And then you are going to go over to QuickBooks Online and refresh or maybe log out and sign in again. And make sure all your data is there. So youre going to want to kind of do a side-by-side comparison to make sure your income statement and your balance sheet, the general ledger, all match what is inside QuickBooks Desktop. I wouldnt recommend like a super thorough craziness, go through every line item. Youre going to be able to tell if things are in there by what the balance sheet income statement look like, the general ledger. If everything matches, everything balances, everythings reconciled still, you should be fine. And then you will go over to "manage my users" with the, theres a little gear icon in the upper right. nnAnd you are going to manage your users and invite your friendly CPA firm, Kruze Consulting, to your accounts. Very, very easy. You do it as an accountant user. This, people dont know this necessarily, but being an account user gives you some superpowers. We can see all of the clients that we work with in one, you know, one giant console, and we can provision permission for each member of our team through that accountant console. So super important to give your accountant access as an accountant, not just as a normal user, because thatll make it kind of difficult for them, especially if youre doing this to get a quote. 

Like the context of this for us, a lot of times, if someone has been maybe working with like an old school accountant who only knows desktop, or maybe they have been doing it themselves, and theyre looking to professionalize their bookkeeping and taxes. And so this whole kind of jump through these hoops is all to get it into a QuickBooks Online version, where we can easily deliver a quote and tell you whats going on in your book. So I hope this helps, again Intuit does have some really good resources, including some videos on this. So Im not going to really do like a play by play, insert a play by play video here. But this commentary should be very helpful for you. nnBecause theres a couple of places where it gets a little sticky and you know, kind of a hard time knowing where to go. So I hope this helps. If you have any questions, hit us up at kruzeconsulting.com. Well help you out and wish you the best of luck, thanks.,
